                </a></li></ul></div><p><strong>Figure 1.  <span>Strategy for amplification and labeling of pathogen-specific target.</span></strong></p><a id="article1.body1.sec2.sec2.fig1.caption1.p1" name="article1.body1.sec2.sec2.fig1.caption1.p1"></a><p>The one-tube RT-PCR reaction includes three stages: A) Reverse transcription reaction to produce first strand cDNA for viral targets (vRNA); B) Low temperature (56°C), exponential amplification of target and C) High temperature (68°C), linear amplification to product single-strand, biotin-labeled target. Target is labeled by incorporation of biotin-14-dCTP during amplification or by the use of biotinylated reverse primers.</p>
